body_html:
@jart I don't think this is using any of tf.contrib, is it? FWIW, the Windows releases include tf.contrib (via the CMake build), but the Bazel build doesn't include it—IIRC because the method of integrating tf.load_op_library()-based extensions doesn't currently work in Bazel.

On the original issue, I think this race is "benign", and the error messages are printed in a situation where the queue-runner for tf.train.string_input_producer() is terminated by closing the session. I think the errors would be avoided if you add num_epochs=1 to thetf.train.string_input_producer() arguments.

body:
@jart I don't think this is using any of `tf.contrib`, is it? FWIW, the Windows releases include `tf.contrib` (via the CMake build), but the Bazel build doesn't include it—IIRC because the method of integrating `tf.load_op_library()`-based extensions doesn't currently work in Bazel.

On the original issue, I think this race is "benign", and the error messages are printed in a situation where the queue-runner for `tf.train.string_input_producer()` is terminated by closing the session. I think the errors would be avoided if you add `num_epochs=1` to the`tf.train.string_input_producer()` arguments.
